  "lessons_for_session_3": [
    "CIK identity is the primary key, not ticker \u2014 the differ must compare CIK sets between snapshots, not ticker sets, or it will miss renames classified as REMOVE+ADD.",
    "For ADD events whose source revision left date_added blank, fall back to the revision timestamp as effective_date.",
    "The hybrid filter has a tunable false-positive rate (~30-40%). The differ MUST be cheap to run on a no-change snapshot \u2014 parsed-set comparison only, no further work.",
    "Some comment-only matches are genuine non-events (e.g., article-meta edits matching keyword \"added\" on tags). These are filtered downstream by the differ producing no set change."
